Compares two objects that must be date-times, but ignores the date part and only returns the result of the time comparison. The resolution is to the second; milliseconds are ignored (they are not explicitly rounded).

Parameters:
value1 - The first object to be compared.
value2 - The second object to be compared.
Returns:
The result of the comparison: <0 if the first time is earlier than the second, 0 if they are the same time, >0 if the first is later than the second.
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if either object is null.
java.lang.ClassCastException - if either object is not a curam.util.type.DateTime.
